          "muted": true,
          "reported_by_user": false,
          "raw_body": "She is holding March expo puts. If we V shape recover into March OPEX then that’s a waste of cash.\n\nI thought she was thinking that we see a subtle decline lower with potentially violent rallies like Friday, chopping in a “bull flag”/triangle like  pattern into March OPEX… only instead of breaking out to the upside (as is usually the case with a bull flag), we breakout to the downside in an elevator like capitulation decline.\n\nShe has stated this environment would be great for keeping put option premiums high while allowing them to decay so bears don’t make money.\n\nAnd since the call side is underpriced, there will be more opportunity for “arbitrage” by taking advantage of those violent rallies.\n\nBut given this I don’t know why she would be holding long dated March Expo puts if they will be prone to decay and expiring worthless. I would assume spot is getting close to where she bought them last Wednesday.",
